
// Logic of Second Highest Element

// Step 1: Find the highest value in the array.

Create a variable `max` and assign it the value of the first element of the array.
Traverse the array using a loop.
If `arr[i]` is greater than `max`, update `max` with `arr[i]`.

// Step 2: Find the value that is smaller than `max` but greater than all other values.

Assume the first element is the second highest value.
Traverse the array from the first index to the last index.
If `arr[i]` is smaller than `max`, compare it with `secondHighest`.
If `arr[i]` is greater than `secondHighest`, update `secondHighest` with `arr[i]`.
